The fashion industry is about to witness the opening of a brand new fashion academy in Surulere Lagos, this December. The beautiful lady behind the school revealed a lot about her project. Yewande Hakeem-Habeeb, the Creative Director of Qubraz Designs and Fashion Academy said the new Qubraz Flagship Store/Fashion Academy will offer training on how to be a professional designer, luxurious outfits, bridals, wholesales, ready to wear outfits for retailers and end-users. The store will be opened on the 15th of December 2019 in grand style. “As part of our social responsibility at Qubraz Designs, scholarship will be given on 3months/ 6months tailoring and embellishments techniques to selected few. Free gift on every purchase made on that day. “At Qubraz Designs we adorn luxurious fabrics with unexpected details, such as hand stitching and intriguing accents to add dimension and personality to each piece with an emphasis on shape and silhouette. At Qubraz Designs, customer satisfaction is highly guaranteed. Our core values at Qubraz Designs we love what we do we, we work hard, we pay attention to details, we have fun, and we give back,” Hakeem-Habeeb said. Speaking on the kind of outfits she designs, she said at Qubraz Designs they make trendy ready to wear and luxurious made to measure outfits at pocket-friendly prices, adding that they also offer training on how to become a professional designer. 